                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>Rhymed note, written in the main hand, mentioning the name of scribe ʾaläqa Mängäša Tämnet and his lord ras Sǝbḥat.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters and words written interlineally: e.g., fols. 4va, 28ra, 29rb, 40rb, 105ra, 109vb.&#xD;
- Immediate correction is indicated by thin lines above and below the letter to be cancelled on fol. 57ra.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated name (of the donor’s wife) are left unfilled: fols. 21rb, 22va, 24va, 36rab.&#xD;
- Sketch for an ornamental band on fol. 29r, in ink. &#xD;
- Short note in Tǝgrǝñña on fol. 28rb in recent hand: የመዝገብ፡ ቁጥር፡ ሽህ፡ ተ፶፮ ተሕሣሥ፡ ፳፮ቀን፡ ፵፪ዓመተ. &#xD;
- Crude note in pencil on fol. 11r. &#xD;
- A paper print with a devotional image of the Virgin and Child (with legends in Latin) is kept in the Ms.</item>
                     </list>
